The Journal of Thoracic and Cardiovascular Surgery (print: , online: ) is a monthly peer-reviewed medical journal covering cardiology, general surgery, pulmonary medicine, and vascular disease published by Elsevier. It is an official journal of the American Association for Thoracic Surgery and The Western Thoracic Surgical Association. The journal was established in 1931 as the "Journal of Thoracic Surgery". According to the "Journal Citation Reports", its 2013 impact factor is 3.991, ranking it 12th out of 202 journals in the category "Surgery", 9th out of 53 journals in the category "Respiratory system", and 28th out of 125 journals in the category "Cardiac & cardiovascular systems".

Saints Severinus, Exuperius, and Felician were martyrs put to death under Emperor Marcus Aurelius at Vienne, Gaul.
